Mr David Abuluya, the proprietor of Nacabs Polytechnic, Akwanga, Nasarawa State, has advised students and other Nigerians against drug-related issues in the interest of their health Mr Abuluya gave the warning in Akwanga when an NGO, Audu Tanko Hope Foundation ( ATHF) took an awareness campaign against drug abuse to the school on Thursday. According to him, drug abuse has affected the lives of my students and youths negatively, hence the need for the students and youths to avert it at all times. The proprietor who commended the foundation for the awareness campaign to the school; called for its sustenance. ” I want to appreciate the foundation for creating awareness against drug abuse in the school. “This will go a long way in fighting the menace in the society as my school is 75 per cent drug-free. ” I also want to advise students and other Nigerians to stay clear of drug abuse in the interest of their health and for social development,” he said. Also speaking, Dr Gonji Thomas, the Medica Superintendent, Model Hospital Akwanga while sensitizing the students against drug abuse, also urged them to avoid of hard drugs. -Advertisement- POLL ” Some students are taught that taking stimulants will make them read hard and pass examinations with higher grades, it is not true. ” Such students are just deceiving themselves and their brains. The addiction effect of its will lead to madness and If they are not properly rehabilitated, they will end up dying, ” he said. Earlier. Amb. Philip Audu-Tanko, the Chief Executive Officer of the Foundation said that they were at the Polytechnic to educate the students against drug abuse. He also said that the visit to the school was part of the foundation’s commitment to observing the International Day of Drug Abuse. The chief executive officer also urged the students and other youths to abstain from drugs abuse., adding that ” we must say no to drug abuse,”